    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Waste silk; spun from the shortest fibers of the waste leftover after making the slightly more valuable schappe silk. The fibers measure 3 to 5 centimeters. This shows less luster than the unspun filament of the cocoon.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
